reason.tex:
%text If $\itanx + \itany = c$, then % \begin{align}
&\ddx \itanx + \ddx \itany = \underbrace{\ddx c = 0}_{\ddx\text{constant} = 0}\\ &\implies \frac{1}{1+x^2} + \underbrace{\frac{1}{1+y^2}\cdot \dydx}_{\text{Chain Rule}} = 0 \\ &\text{or }\frac{1}{1+y^2}\cdot \dydx = -\frac{1}{1+x^2} \\ &\text{or }\trma\cdot dy = -\trmb\cdot dx \\ &\text{or }\trma\cdot dy + \trmb\cdot dx = 0 \end{align} %text In other words, if \[\quad \trma\cdot dy + \trmb\cdot dx = 0\] is the differential equation, then
\[ \quad \itanx + \itany = c\] is the general solution%
